sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36732
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: EfeU iron (II) transporter + 5' UTR (medium) + terminator + Fur promoter + Gemini
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part has our actuator and sensor combined into a single sequence, followed by Gemini.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom McLaughlin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36731
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: EfeU elemental iron (II) transporter + 5' UTR (medium) + terminator + Fur promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part has our actuator and sensor combined into a single sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom McLaughlin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: After the terminator of the actual part, we have the Fur promoter. We're planning to place a universal sensor before this part (to trigger expression of EfeU) and a universal actuator after (to trigger expression of a signal when iron is low).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36709
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A medium strength RBS expressing Gemini, ending with a strong terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeff Quinn and Wyatt Woodson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Gemini, a Bifunctional Enzymatic and Fluorescent Reporter of Gene Expression. PLOS One. Lance Martin et al.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36729
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: EfeU elemental iron (II) transporter + 5' UTR (medium) + terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part has the EfeU iron transporter downstream from a medium 5' Bicistronic UTR. There is a terminator at the end.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom McLaughlin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We are hoping that this 5' UTR will cause enough expression of the EfeU protein to measure, without producing so much that the organism dies due to excessive iron uptake or other ion imbalances.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_E0051
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a fusion protein between GFP and the alpha fragment of lacZ. It can be measured via fluorescence from GFP or through an assay for beta-galactosidase in a strain containing the omega fragment of lacZ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Austin Che
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: amino acids 3-60 from lacZ and amino acids 2-end of GFP (E0043)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The amino acid linker AGGSEGGGSEHHHHHHGSE is between the lacZa and GFP. The 6-his can also facilitate detection on a Western blot, for purification, etc.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pPS-PCR is a promoter which is controlled by the iron-repressive transcription factor, Fur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brent Townshend
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: 1. Gunter K, Toupet C, Schupp T. sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli RNA pol transcription terminator designed and tested by Guillaume Cambray at BIOFAB Emeryville. Based on the natural E. coli rnpB T1 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Guillaume Cambray et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36042
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the reconstructed gene for the EfeU iron transporter. This gene is inactive in K-12 strain E. coli, but has been characterized in the Nissle 1917 strain. (Grobe, Scherer et al. PMID: 16987175.)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom McLaughlin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From wild-type Nissle 1917 E. coli. The sequence came from the Ecogene entry EG13860.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence was conceptually reconstructed from the frame-shifted version. The Ecogene entry has an "N" for the nucleotide which is uncertain, but a comment in that entry says that the correct amino acid is likely glycine. Thus we chose N = G in the final sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (medium), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Vivek Mutalik et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville.
